cscie97.asn4.ecommerce.product

Class ContentSearch

  • java.lang.Object
    • cscie97.asn4.ecommerce.product.ContentSearch

  • public class ContentSearch
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a user search query of the IProductAPI for Content items that match the criteria in the search object. Since content objects will be changing (adding new ContentType in the future to add more types that may have different attributes, the ContentSearch object can abstract away the differences in types and also simplify the querying of content rather than pass around very long parameter lists to query (just pass around a ContentSearch object instead). Future expandability and features based on this object could be things such as:
    • logging search queries to the ProductAPI
    • saving and analyzing historical queries for trends, popular searches, terms, etc.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    David Killeffer <rayden7@gmail.com>
    See Also:
    IProductAPI, Content, Application, Ringtone, Wallpaper

    • Constructor Detail

      • ContentSearch

        public ContentSearch()
        Public class constructor with no arguments. The no-arg constructor is used for building out new ContentSearch objects that get modified as the SearchEngine loops over a CSV query import file and constructs new ContentSearch objects for each unique search.

      • ContentSearch

        public ContentSearch(java.lang.String rawQuery,
             java.util.Set<java.lang.String> categories,
             java.lang.String textSearch,
             int minimumRating,
             float maximumPrice,
             java.util.Set<java.lang.String> supportedLanguages,
             java.util.Set<Country> countries,
             java.util.Set<Device> devices,
             java.util.Set<ContentType> contentTypes)
        Class constructor. ContentSearch objects are created by the SearchEngine to capture the search criteria that is from the input CSV files, and then the ContentSearch objects are passed to the Singleton instance of the ProductAPI for executing the actual content search.
        Parameters:
        rawQuery - the actual raw string query passed (including commas)
        categories - distinct categories to search for, pipe-separated
        textSearch - the text to search across name, author, and description for
        minimumRating - the minimum rating that all matching content items should be, or higher; defaults to 6 so that ALL content items which are on the 1-5 rating scale will be included
        maximumPrice - the maximum price to match content items on; defaults to -1 if not passed so that ALL content items will be included
        supportedLanguages - set of languages that found content items must support
        countries - set of countries that matching content items must be able to be exported to
        devices - set of devices that matching content items must support
        contentTypes - set of content types that matching content items must be
